{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01WwaSsdNjBhaQgwY4z1BQBz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0183PVhyZzaSAwDMcY1Dhkf3","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Mushroom Risotto.generated.21.txt","content":"Page 142\n\nMUSHROOM RISOTTO\n\nRecipe Category: MAIN COURSES\nCuisine: Italian | Serves: 4 | Prep Time: 15 min | Cook Time: 30 min\n\nIngredients:\n- 1½ cups Arborio rice\n- 4 cups warm vegetable or chicken stock\n- 1 pound mixed mushrooms, sliced\n- 1 medium onion, finely diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- ½ cup dry white wine\n- ½ cup Parmesan cheese, grated\n- 3 tablespoons butter\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- ¼ teaspoon saffron threads (optional) 456\n\nInstructions:\n1. Heat stock in separate pot, keep warm\n2. Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in large saucepan over medium heat\n3. Sauté mushrooms until golden, about 5 minutes. Remove and set aside\n4. Add remaining butter to pan\n5. Sauté onion and garlic until soft, about 3 minutes (Page 143)\n6. Add rice and stir constantly for 1-2 minutes\n7. Pour in wine and stir until absorbed\n8. Add warm stock one ladle at a time, stirring frequently\n9. Wait until each ladle of stock is absorbed before adding next\n10. Continue for about 18-20 minutes until rice is creamy but still al dente 789\n11. Stir in mushrooms, Parmesan, remaining butter\n12. Season with salt and pepper\n13. Garnish with parsley\n14. Serve immediately\n\nTips:\n- Quality Arborio rice is essential\n- Risotto cannot be rushed - constant stirring is key\n- Use high quality stock for best flavor\n- Saffron adds traditional Milanese touch but is optional 321\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":754,"cache_read_input_tokens":89442,"cache_crea